The paper proposes a novel metric for comparing symbolic sequences that can be optimized with gradient methods, which suggests it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the analysis of genetic sequences, which falls under the data structures (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses clustering of sequences, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
